  "prompt": "Where can I get a large corpus of news articles with pictures?",
  "response": "There are several sources where you can obtain a large corpus of news articles along with accompanying images. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n1. **News API**: This is a popular service that provides access to news articles from various sources. You can filter articles based on criteria like date, sources, and more. While the API primarily offers text, some articles may include URLs to images.\n\n2. **Common Crawl**: This is a web archive that provides a large dataset of web pages, which includes news articles. While it does not specifically curate images, you can extract articles and use image search engines or APIs like Google Images to find related images.\n\n3. **GNews API**: Similar to News API, GNews provides a way to pull news articles from various sources. Some articles may include images, and you can specify certain criteria in your queries.\n\n4. **Twitter and Social Media**: Many news outlets share articles and images on social media. You could use the Twitter API to scrape tweets that contain links to articles, along with any images that are included in those tweets.\n\n5. **Kaggle Datasets**: Kaggle often has datasets shared by the community, including news articles and images. You can search their dataset repository for any that meet your needs.\n\n6. **Image and News Aggregators**: Websites like Flickr or Wikimedia Commons may have news-related images that you can link to or use in conjunction with articles.\n\n7. **Government and Educational Sources**: Some universities and government organizations maintain archives of news articles which may include images for research purposes.\n\nRemember to always check the licensing and usage rights for any data or images you collect, especially if you plan to use them in a project or for commercial purposes.",
